table_foot: Notes: Data are presented as mean (SD) unless otherwise stated. Comparisons were made using analysis of variance (ANOVA) and the chi‐square test where appropriate. p values <.05 are marked in bold italics. p values <.05 resulting from post‐hoc Tukey analysis are labeled as given below.Abbreviations: AD, Alzheimer's disease; NC, normal cognition; SIVD, subcortical ischemic vascular disease.aBetween SIVD and NC.bBetween AD and NC.cBetween SIVD and AD.
